CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Counties – No–Cost Preventive Cancer Screenings for Volunteer and Retired
3 Volunteer Firefighters
4 FOR the purpose of requiring counties in which a volunteer fire company is located to offer
5 no–cost preventive cancer screenings in accordance with certain guidelines to
6 volunteer firefighters volunteering and retired volunteer firefighters who
7 volunteered with the volunteer fire company; authorizing a county to satisfy the
8 requirement by providing a certain annual examination or applying for a certain
9 grant; requiring the volunteer fire companies to maintain a certain list of volunteer
10 firefighters and retired volunteer firefighters and provide the list, annually and on
11 request, to the county in which the volunteer fire company is located; requiring the
12 counties to maintain the list provided; and generally relating to the provision of
13 no–cost preventive cancer screenings for volunteer and retired volunteer firefighters
14 by counties.
15 BY adding to
16 Article – Local Government
17 Section 9–115
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2013 Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
21 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0579*

2 SENATE BILL 579
1 Article – Local Government
2 9–115.
3 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
4 INDICATED.
5 (2) “RETIRED VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL
6 WHO IS A RETIRED FIREFIGHTER WHO:
7 (I) VOLUNTEERED WITH A VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY IN A
8 COUNTY;
9 (II) WAS ACTIVELY INVOLVED IN FIRE SUPPRESSION WHILE
10 VOLUNTEERING WITH THE VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY; AND
11 (III) HAS RECEIVED BENEFITS UNDER A LENGTH OF SERVICE
12 AWARD PROGRAM FOR AT LEAST 5 YEARS.
13 (2) (3) “VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY” INCLUDES A VOLUNTEER
14 FIRE DEPARTMENT.
15 (3) (4) “VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS
16 A FIREFIGHTER ACTIVELY INVOLVED IN FIRE SUPPRESSION AND VOLUNTEERING
17 WITH A VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY IN A COUNTY.
18 (B) (1) EACH COUNTY IN WHICH A VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY IS
19 LOCATED SHALL OFFER NO–COST PREVENTIVE CANCER SCREENINGS IN
20 ACCORDANCE WITH THE LATEST SCREENING GUIDELINES ISSUED BY THE
21 INTERNATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF FIRE FIGHTERS TO EACH VOLUNTEER
22 FIREFIGHTER WHO VOLUNTEERS AND EACH RETIRED VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTER
23 WHO VOLUNTEERED WITH THE VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY.
24 (2) EACH VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY SHALL:
25 (I) MAINTAIN AN UP–TO–DATE LIST OF VOLUNTEER
26 FIREFIGHTERS WHO ARE VOLUNTEERING AND RETIRED VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTERS
27 WHO VOLUNTEERED WITH THE VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY; AND
28 (II) PROVIDE THE LIST TO THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE
29 VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY IS LOCATED:
30 1. ON OR BEFORE OCTOBER 1 EACH YEAR; AND

SENATE BILL 579 3
1 2. ON REQUEST OF THE COUNTY.
2 (3) EACH COUNTY IN WHICH A VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY IS
3 LOCATED SHALL MAINTAIN A LIST OF ALL VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTERS WHO
4 VOLUNTEER AND ALL RETIRED VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTERS WHO VOLUNTEERED IN
5 THE COUNTY AS PROVIDED BY EACH VOLUNTEER FIRE COMPANY LOCATED IN THE
6 COUNTY UNDER PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION.
7 (C) A COUNTY MAY SATISFY THE REQUIREMENT IN SUBSECTION (B)(1) OF
8 THIS SECTION BY:
9 (1) PROVIDING A NO–COST ANNUAL EXAMINATION TO VOLUNTEER
10 FIREFIGHTERS AND RETIRED VOLUNTEER FIREFIGHTERS THAT INCLUDES
11 PREVENTIVE CANCER SCREENINGS FOR FIREFIGHTERS IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE
12 LATEST SCREENING GUIDELINES ISSUED BY THE INTERNATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF
13 FIRE FIGHTERS; OR
14 (2) APPLYING FOR A GRANT UNDER TITLE 13, SUBTITLE 40 OF THE
15 HEALTH – GENERAL ARTICLE TO PAY FOR INNOVATIVE CANCER SCREENING
16 TECHNOLOGIES, INCLUDING A MULTICANCER EARLY DETECTION BLOOD TEST.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
18 1, 2026.
Approved:
